{
  "texts": [
    "While rating tasks offer participants the latitude to distinguish varying degrees of grammaticality, they also introduce questions concerning the consistency of participants in correlating numerical scores with perceived acceptability.",
    "For instance, does a sentence scored at five genuinely seem less acceptable than a sentence rated six later in the same experiment?",
    "Given this, it's paramount to supplement the rating tasks with a forced-choice task (FC task).",
    "This format affords participants less interpretative flexibility and thereby ensures heightened within-participant reliability.",
    "In this experiment, we replicated the FC task in Sprouse et al. (2013) with ChatGPT serving as the participant."
  ]
}